The paper discusses the handling of semantic heterogeneity in information retrieval, which is a common problem in the field of information retrieval (IR). The paper describes a set of extraction rules developed for the domain of Social Sciences, which suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the use of intellectual, statistical, and neural network transfer modules for mapping between different terminologies, which suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DL (Machine Learning), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
